casebody.data:
Cleveland Bar Association v. Faison.

[Cite as Cleveland Bar Assn. v. Faison (1994), 70 Ohio St.3d 636.]

(No. 94-1376 Submitted September 13, 1994 Decided November 9, 1994.) *637Ticktin, Baron, Koepper Co., L.P.A., and Engeline Koepper; Michael Wypasek; and Patrick Gannon, for relator. Per Curiam.

We concur in the findings and recommendation of the board. Jacquelyn J.C. Faison is hereby indefinitely suspended from the practice of law. Costs taxed to respondent.

Judgment accordingly.

Moyer, C.J., A.W. Sweeney, Douglas, Wright, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney and Pfeifer, JJ., concur.
